A group including Fort Worth, Texas, investors Sid and Lee Bass said it boosted its stake in American Medical International Inc. to 12.7% of the company's 69 million common shares outstanding. 

In a filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission, the group, which previously held an 11.3% stake, said it now owns 8,743,000 shares, including 110,000 shares purchased between Sept. 15 and Sept. 19 for $21.94 to $22.56. 

Earlier this year, the group said that it might attempt to seek a controlling position in American Medical.
A spokesman for the Basses declined to comment on the boost in their stake. 

In composite trading on the New York Stock Exchange, Beverly Hills, Calif.-based American Medical closed yesterday at $23, up 37.5 cents. 

